      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Trim the ends off your <strong>Brussels sprouts</strong>, then chop in half lengthways</p><p>Trim, then chop your <strong>spring onions</strong> into thirds</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1667324163588-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1667324163588-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1667324163588-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1667324163588-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1667324163588-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped sprouts</strong> and <strong>chopped spring onion</strong> to a<strong> baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray</p><p>Add a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray in the oven and cook for 15-20 min or until the sprouts are tender and slightly crispy – these are your<strong> roasted sprouts & spring onion</strong></p><p>Once tender, remove the tray from the oven and set aside</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1667324167384-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1667324167384-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1667324167384-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1667324167384-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1667324167384-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the vegetables are roasting, peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Slice your <strong>red chilli[es]</strong> finely</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1667324171111-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1667324171111-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1667324171111-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1667324171111-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1667324171111-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Squeeze the pouch[es]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>of <strong>cooked white long grain rice</strong> to separate the grains</p><p>Tear the top corner of the pouch[es]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>(just a little!) and <strong>microwave</strong> for 2 min or until piping hot</p><p>Tip: If you're cooking two or more pouches, pop them in together but increase the microwave cook time accordingly</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1667324175409-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1667324175409-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1667324175409-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1667324175409-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1667324175409-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add<strong> half </strong>the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>(save the rest for later!)<strong> </strong>and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add your<strong> white long grain rice</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until warmed through – this is your <strong>garlic rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1667324180357-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1667324180357-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1667324180357-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1667324180357-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1667324180357-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a separate, medium-sized pot over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>remaining chopped garlic </strong>and <strong>cornflour</strong> to the pot with your <strong>rice vinegar</strong>, <strong>red</strong> <strong>chilli relish</strong>, <strong>half</strong> your <strong>tamari soy sauce </strong>(you'll use the rest later!), <strong>sriracha </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>roasted peanuts</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until thickened</p><p>Once thickened, add the <strong>roasted sprouts & spring onions </strong>to the pot and mix it all together – these are your <strong>Kung Pao Brussels sprouts</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1667324184424-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1667324184424-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1667324184424-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1667324184424-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1667324184424-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the garlic rice has warmed through, add your <strong>blanched peas</strong>,<strong> </strong>your <strong>toasted sesame oil</strong>, the <strong>remaining tamari soy sauce</strong> and cook for 2-3 min until everything is combined</p><p>Once combined, push the rice to one side of the pan and crack your <strong>egg[s] </strong>into the other side</p><p>Stir the<strong> </strong>egg[s]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>with a wooden spoon to break the yolk[s] and cook for 1-2 min until it resembles scrambled egg, then mix it all through the rice – this is your <strong>egg fried rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1667324188843-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1667324188843-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1667324188843-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1667324188843-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1667324188843-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> Kung Pao Brussels sprouts</strong> over the<strong> egg fried rice</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>sliced chilli </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!)</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
